Package org.neo4j.index.internal.gbptree

Interface Writer<KEY,​VALUE>

  • Type Parameters:
    KEY - type of keys
    VALUE - type of values
    All Superinterfaces:
    AutoCloseable, Closeable
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    GBPTree.SingleWriter
    public interface Writer<KEY,​VALUE>
extends Closeable
    Able to merge(Object, Object, ValueMerger) and remove(Object) key/value pairs into a GBPTree. After all modifications have taken place the writer must be closed, typically using try-with-resource clause.

    • Method Detail

      • put

        void put​(KEY key,
         VALUE value)
        Associate given key with given value. Any existing value associated with key will be overwritten.
        Parameters:
        key - key to associate with value
        value - value to associate with key
        Throws:
        UncheckedIOException - on index access error.

      • merge

        void merge​(KEY key,
           VALUE value,
           ValueMerger<KEY,​VALUE> valueMerger)
        If the key doesn't already exist in the index the key will be added and the value associated with it. If the key already exists then its existing value will be merged with the given value, using the ValueMerger.
        Parameters:
        key - key for which to merge values.
        value - value to merge with currently associated value for the key.
        valueMerger - ValueMerger to consult if key already exists.
        Throws:
        UncheckedIOException - on index access error.
        See Also:
        ValueMerger.merge(Object, Object, Object, Object)

      • mergeIfExists

        void mergeIfExists​(KEY key,
                   VALUE value,
                   ValueMerger<KEY,​VALUE> valueMerger)
        If the key already exists then its existing value will be merged with the given value, using the ValueMerger. If the key doesn't exist then no changes will be made and false will be returned.
        Parameters:
        key - key for which to merge values.
        value - value to merge with currently associated value for the key.
        valueMerger - ValueMerger to consult if key already exists.
        Throws:
        UncheckedIOException - on index access error.
        See Also:
        ValueMerger.merge(Object, Object, Object, Object)

      • remove

        VALUE remove​(KEY key)
        Removes a key, returning it's associated value, if found.
        Parameters:
        key - key to remove.
        Returns:
        value which was associated with the remove key, if found, otherwise null.
        Throws:
        UncheckedIOException - on index access error.
